    "Hardwood floors are Scotland's most popular premium flooring choice — particularly in Edinburgh's Georgian and Victorian tenements (original pine boards), Glasgow's sandstone terraces (oak and ash), and Aberdeen's granite-built homes (mahogany-stained softwoods in older properties, modern oak in new builds). They're beautiful, durable, and add real value to a property — but only if they're cared for. Neglected hardwood floors develop wear patterns in traffic areas (kitchen-to-doorway paths become visibly lighter), grit scratches the finish (allowing moisture to penetrate and stain the wood), and UV fades the colour ( rugs left in place for years leave permanent light patches when moved). A floor that's 30 years old can look 100 years old without proper care — or it can look brand new with it.",
