    "Blind cleaning matters more than most people realise. Blinds are exposed to everything in the room — kitchen grease, bathroom moisture, living room dust, bedroom skin cells, pet dander — and they collect it all. A typical Venetian blind in a family home has 5-10 grams of dust per slat after a year (multiply by 20-30 slats per blind, and that's 100-300 grams per blind). That dust is a reservoir for dust mites, pollen, pet allergens, and bacteria — and every time you open or close the blind, you redistribute it into the air. For anyone with asthma, allergies, or respiratory sensitivities, blind cleaning is essential, not optional.",
