    "What sets us apart is the technique. We use ultrasonic cleaning for Venetian and vertical blinds — a process that immerses the blind in a tank of water with ultrasonic waves and a mild detergent. The ultrasonic waves create microscopic bubbles that penetrate every crevice, lifting dirt that hand-cleaning can't reach. The blind comes out spotless, dried, and rehung in around 60 minutes per blind (we typically take them down and rehang the same day, or take them to our workshop for next-day return). For fabric blinds (roller, Roman, pleated), we use hand-cleaning with specialist fabric-safe products — never soaking, never scrubbing. We're careful with delicate fabrics, with fire-retardant coatings (some cleaning products strip them), and with operating mechanisms (we don't force stiff cords). All work is guaranteed.",
